# The Problem - if there are updation coming for an element every 1 sec then instead of updating every other update we can wait and then update the latest update.

# Solution -React Fibre - A fiber represents a unit of work.

# React fibre helps us to enable React to take advantage of scheduling. Specifically, we need to be able to

pause work and come back to it later.
assign priority to different types of work.
reuse previously completed work.
abort work if it's no longer needed. 

# virtual Dom - .createRoot method creates a DOM for React and instead of updating the entire dom Structure it only updates the differences in virtual dom and original dom. It also helps in rendering faster 